    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Electronics Engineering?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Electronics Engineering is a specialized branch of electrical engineering that focuses on the design, development, and application of electronic circuits, devices, and systems. It involves working with components that control the flow of electrons or other charge carriers in devices, enabling the processing, transmission, and storage of information.</p>
                    <p>As an electronics engineer, you'll work on creating and improving a wide range of technologies, from consumer electronics and communication systems to medical devices and industrial automation. You'll apply principles of physics, mathematics, and computer science to develop innovative solutions that address real-world challenges.</p>
                    <p>This field is at the heart of technological advancement, driving progress in areas such as telecommunications, computing, healthcare, transportation, and entertainment. With the rapid pace of technological change, electronics engineers are constantly learning and adapting to new developments in materials, devices, and design methodologies.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="image-content">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517420704952-d9f39e95b43e?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Electronics Engineering">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Areas Section -->
    <section class="section bg-dark" id="key-areas">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--light-text);">Key Areas of Study</h2>
            <p class="section-intro" style="color: var(--light-text);">Electronics Engineering encompasses several specialized areas that form the foundation of modern electronic systems:</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid three-columns">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> Digital Electronics</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of electronic circuits that operate with discrete signals, using binary logic (0s and 1s) to process and store information. This includes combinational and sequential logic circuits, digital signal processing, and computer architecture.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Logic Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Boolean algebra, logic gates, flip-flops, registers</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Digital Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Microprocessors, memory systems, digital interfaces</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">FPGA Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Hardware description languages (VHDL, Verilog)</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-wave-square"></i> Analog Electronics</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of electronic circuits that process continuous signals, dealing with variables that change over a continuous range. This includes amplifiers, filters, oscillators, and power supplies that manipulate voltage and current levels.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Circuit Analysis</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Kirchhoff's laws, network theorems, transient analysis</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Amplifier Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Operational amplifiers, feedback systems, gain control</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Filter Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Active and passive filters, frequency response</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-satellite-dish"></i> Communication Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of transmitting and receiving information over various media, including wired and wireless channels. This includes modulation techniques, signal processing, and network protocols for reliable data transfer.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Signal Modulation</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">AM, FM, digital modulation techniques</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Wireless Communications</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">RF design, antennas, propagation models</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Communication Networks</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Protocols, network architecture, data transmission</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cards-grid three-columns" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-robot"></i> Embedded Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of specialized computing systems designed for dedicated functions within larger mechanical or electrical systems. This includes microcontrollers, real-time operating systems, and interface design for various applications.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Microcontroller Programming</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">ARM, AVR, PIC architectures and programming</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Real-Time Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">RTOS, scheduling, resource management</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Interfacing</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Sensors, actuators, communication protocols</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-microchip"></i> VLSI Design</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of designing and creating integrated circuits by combining thousands to billions of transistors into a single chip. This includes semiconductor physics, circuit design, and fabrication processes for modern ICs.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">IC Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Transistor-level design, standard cells, IP blocks</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Physical Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Layout, floor planning, routing, verification</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Semiconductor Processes</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Fabrication techniques, process integration</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-cogs"></i> Control Systems</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of managing, commanding, directing, or regulating the behavior of devices or systems using control loops. This includes feedback mechanisms, stability analysis, and controller design for various applications.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">System Modeling</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Transfer functions, state-space representation</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Controller Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">PID controllers, state feedback, optimal control</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Digital Control</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Discrete-time systems, digital implementation</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

